    {
      "id": "sybil_14_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "Available is a 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the iconic 13B-REW twin-rotor power plant. This example retains its sophisticated sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, providing a seamless transition and robust boost throughout the rev range. The chassis dynamics are preserved by a four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the 50:50 weight distribution is fully utilized in high-lateral-G maneuvers. Recent preventative maintenance includes a comprehensive vacuum line 'rat's nest' simplification and a cooling system upgrade with a dual-pass aluminum radiator to manage thermal loads. Mechanical integrity is verified by consistent compression results across all rotor faces, indicating healthy apex seals. While the paint exhibits minor road-going patina, the drivetrain remains tight and responsive, offering a pure analog driving experience for the discerning rotary enthusiast.",
